Archive - Michael Laudrup scores against Spain at 1988 Euros
Swansea City managerial candidate Michael Laudrupscores an equalising goal for Denmark in their 3-2 defeat by Spain in their opening game of the 1988 European Championship.BBC Sport Wales understands Swans' chairman Huw Jenkins has held an overseas meeting with the former Real Mallorca and Spartak Moscow coach.Laudrup, who used to play for Juventus, Barcelona and Real Madrid, has previously spoken of a desire to manage in the Premier League.Available to UK users only.